Date: Sat, 19 Aug 2000 20:54:36 -0400
From: Marjorie P. Pollack <pollackmp@mindspring.com>
Source: Xinhua News Agency, filed: Friday Aug 18 2000 1:12 AM EST [edited

30 People Killed by Encephalitis in Nepal
-----------------------------------------
At least 30 people have been killed by encephalitis in the Terai plain of
southern Nepal since the monsoon season began in mid-June, according to
reports reaching here Friday. The outbreak of encephalitis has claimed the
lives of 20 people in the Chitwan district bordering India, said the
official Rising Nepal daily.
The [Rising Nepal Daily reported that with [increasing numbers of
encephalitis patients [seeking hospital treatment, local hospitals are
facing shortage of beds and manpower. Meanwhile, 10 encephalitis deaths
were reported in Terai districts including Morang, Sunsari, Siraha,
Saptari, Udaypur and Kailali. Encephalitis claims several hundred lives in
southern Nepal every year during the monsoon season that lasts from
mid-June to the end of September.
